      "id": "E2-08-Q1",
      "type": "short-answer",
      "totalMarks": 4,
      "commandWord": "find",
      "difficulty": "medium",
      "questionText": "$y$ is directly proportional to $x^2$. When $x = 3$, $y = 36$.\n\n(a) Find the formula for $y$ in terms of $x$.\n(b) Find $y$ when $x = 5$.\n(c) Find $x$ when $y = 100$.",
      "answerType": "expression",
      "correctAnswer": "(a) $y = 4x^2$, (b) 100, (c) 5",
      "tolerance": null,
      "unit": null,
      "markScheme": [
        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "$y = kx^2$; $36 = k(9) \\Rightarrow k = 4$" },
        { "mark": "A1", "desc": "(a) $y = 4x^2$ cao" },
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "(b) $y = 4(25) = 100$" },
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "(c) $100 = 4x^2 \\Rightarrow x^2=25 \\Rightarrow x=5$" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "(a) $y = kx^2$; sub $x=3$, $y=36$: $36=9k \\Rightarrow k=4$; formula: $y=4x^2$",
        "(b) $y=4(5)^2=4(25)=100$",
        "(c) $100=4x^2 \\Rightarrow x^2=25 \\Rightarrow x=5$ (taking positive value)"
      ],
      "explanation": "Write $y = kx^2$, find $k$ from the given values, then use the formula."
    },
    {
      "id": "E2-08-Q2",
      "type": "short-answer",
      "totalMarks": 4,
      "commandWord": "find",
      "difficulty": "medium",
      "questionText": "$y$ is inversely proportional to $x$. When $x = 4$, $y = 6$.\n\n(a) Find the formula for $y$ in terms of $x$.\n(b) Find $y$ when $x = 8$.\n(c) Find $x$ when $y = 16$.",
      "answerType": "expression",
      "correctAnswer": "(a) $y = \\dfrac{24}{x}$, (b) 3, (c) 1.5",
      "tolerance": null,
      "unit": null,
      "markScheme": [
        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "$y = \\frac{k}{x}$; $6 = \\frac{k}{4} \\Rightarrow k = 24$" },
        { "mark": "A1", "desc": "(a) $y = \\frac{24}{x}$ cao" },
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "(b) $y = \\frac{24}{8} = 3$" },
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "(c) $16 = \\frac{24}{x} \\Rightarrow x = 1.5$" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "(a) $y=\\frac{k}{x}$; sub $x=4$, $y=6$: $6=\\frac{k}{4} \\Rightarrow k=24$; formula: $y=\\frac{24}{x}$",
        "(b) $y=\\frac{24}{8}=3$",
        "(c) $16=\\frac{24}{x} \\Rightarrow x=\\frac{24}{16}=1.5$"
      ],
      "explanation": "Write $y = \\frac{k}{x}$, find $k$, then use the formula to answer each part."
    },
